23/12/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- The Social Democratic Party decided Monday (22 December) to accept the ruling Socialist Party's (SP) invitation to enter the ruling "Coalition for Integration". The SP had launched a series of negotiations with left-wing groups in an effort to break a political stalemate.
In other news, Greece has agreed to ease the entry regime for Albanian immigrants during the holiday season. The measure, in force until 10 January, is intended to allow Albanian immigrants without the required permits to spend the holidays with their families. (Albanian Daily News - 23/12/03; ATA - 22/12/03)
